    "plan_content": "Here's a summary of the plan I've written:\n\n## Plan Summary\n\n**Only one file changes:** `common/chat.cpp`\n\n### What I found\n\n- The **Ministral 3** specialized handler (lines 825–940) detects templates that have `[SYSTEM_PROMPT]` + `[TOOL_CALLS]` + `[ARGS]` — this matches Devstral and the Ministral/Magistral family.\n- The **Mistral Nemo Instruct 2407** template (the canonical v0.3 format) uses `[INST]/[/INST]` + `[AVAILABLE_TOOLS]` but has **no** `[SYSTEM_PROMPT]` — so it falls through today to the auto-parser.\n- The PEG builder exposes `p.standard_json_tools(...)` (declared in `chat-peg-parser.h:108`) which perfectly handles the `[TOOL_CALLS][{\"name\":…,\"arguments\":…,\"id\":…}]` JSON-array format.\n\n### Two additions (no edits to existing code)\n\n1. **New function** `common_chat_params_init_mistral_instruct_v3` — inserted after line 940 (after `common_chat_params_init_ministral_3`). Uses `common_chat_template_direct_apply_impl` for the prompt and builds a PEG parser with `p.standard_json_tools` for the `[TOOL_CALLS]` JSON-array format. Content-only path uses `p.content(p.rest())`.\n\n2. **New detection block** inside `common_chat_try_specialized_template` — inserted after line 1644 (after the Ministral 3 block). Detects: `[INST]` present + `[AVAILABLE_TOOLS]` present + `[SYSTEM_PROMPT]` **absent**. This is precise: Llama-2 lacks `[AVAILABLE_TOOLS]`, Ministral/Devstral have `[SYSTEM_PROMPT]`, so there's no overlap.",
